# Design locked — Blakey Trades community app (pitch prototype)

design_system: premium-dark (mirrored from client brand, blakeytrades.com)
design_md_ref: premium-dark + bespoke "living market" direction
rationale: |
  Brand is GIVEN by the client (near-black + gold, Sora/Outfit). The app must feel
  like Blakey Trades, so dark+gold is mandated, not a default choice. Distinctiveness
  comes from the SUBJECT (live gold market), not from inventing a new palette:
    - JetBrains Mono for ALL numerics (prices, entry/SL/TP, timers, P&L, ranks) —
      trading data belongs in a tabular mono face. Content-driven, not decorative.
    - Signature: the market is literally alive — animated gold candlestick/price line
      behind Home + Live headers (canvas, reduced-motion aware).
    - Gold-foil sheen reserved ONLY for "earned" moments (Trader of the Week trophy,
      level badges). Everything else stays quiet so the signature lands.
    - Broker-ticket vernacular for trade ideas; session eyebrows (LONDON · LIVE)
      instead of generic 01/02/03 numbering.

